Just a simple property.

00:22:45.206 --> 00:22:46.246
Very easy to do.

00:22:46.766 --> 00:22:47.756
Pretty cool.

00:22:47.756 --> 00:22:49.276
This is new in iOS 7.

00:22:49.666 --> 00:22:52.246
So next we're going to talk
about a different type of ad.

00:22:52.326 --> 00:22:54.656
We've seen a banner
ad which when tapped,

00:22:54.776 --> 00:22:56.816
presents a full screen
advertisement.

00:22:57.266 --> 00:22:58.896
The Interstitial is a
little bit different,

00:22:58.896 --> 00:22:59.826
in that it doesn't have

00:22:59.826 --> 00:23:02.326
that intermediary
view that you tap on.

00:23:02.726 --> 00:23:06.376
It immediately launches into
a full-screen advertisement.

00:23:07.166 --> 00:23:09.826
So what usually happens
is, as you're transitioning

00:23:09.826 --> 00:23:12.806
from one part of your
application into another part,

00:23:13.316 --> 00:23:16.496
you get this full-screen
advertisement up here.

00:23:16.626 --> 00:23:18.946
So this is pretty cool.

00:23:19.626 --> 00:23:24.426
This has been available since
iOS 4.3 on iPad, as of iOS 7,

00:23:24.426 --> 00:23:26.966
this is all also
available on the iPhone,

00:23:27.556 --> 00:23:30.236
so you can start using
this today on iPhone too.

00:23:31.636 --> 00:23:35.076
Now when I talk about
automatic presentation

00:23:35.076 --> 00:23:37.496
of a full-screen view,
when does that happen?

00:23:37.646 --> 00:23:40.716
As of iOS 7, we now
have this new property

00:23:40.716 --> 00:23:42.966
on View Controller
similar to the property

00:23:43.156 --> 00:23:46.836
on the banner ads
called the Interstitial

00:23:46.836 --> 00:23:48.096
Presentation Policy.

00:23:48.446 --> 00:23:52.376
And what the iAd framework is
now able to do for you is watch

00:23:52.376 --> 00:23:54.696
for View Controllers
to become visible,

00:23:55.126 --> 00:23:57.556
and then present an
interstitial ad automatically

00:23:57.886 --> 00:23:59.336
when that view becomes visible.

00:24:00.316 --> 00:24:02.586
So if you've got
a view controller,

00:24:02.586 --> 00:24:04.166
we can say there's two
View Controllers here;

00:24:04.166 --> 00:24:07.086
one is off-screen, the current
View Controller on-screen,

00:24:07.156 --> 00:24:08.866
and the next View
Controller off-screen.

00:24:09.456 --> 00:24:12.136
We want to configure the
Interstitial Presentation Policy

00:24:12.206 --> 00:24:14.886
of the next View
Controller to be automatic.

00:24:15.156 --> 00:24:16.356
We want the iAd framework

00:24:16.356 --> 00:24:18.926
to automatically manage
presentation of an interstitial

00:24:19.276 --> 00:24:24.066
when it's appropriate based
on inventory and minimum time

00:24:24.066 --> 00:24:25.776
between interstitial
presentations.

00:24:26.706 --> 00:24:29.426
Now when we call
pushViewController to present

00:24:29.426 --> 00:24:31.426
that View Controller,

00:24:32.006 --> 00:24:34.306
an interstitial is
automatically presented on top.

00:24:35.246 --> 00:24:38.886
When the user dismisses the
full-screen interstitial,

00:24:39.236 --> 00:24:40.916
they're back to that
next View Controller.

00:24:40.916 --> 00:24:43.326
They're back into the app.

00:24:43.586 --> 00:24:46.466
There's also another option for
applications that are doing,

00:24:46.686 --> 00:24:49.366
maybe single View
Controller style,

00:24:49.436 --> 00:24:51.456
have the single View
Controller architecture.

00:24:51.866 --> 00:24:55.266
Things like games, where
you need to have control

00:24:55.266 --> 00:24:56.806
over the presentation
of the interstitial

00:24:56.806 --> 00:25:00.006
because there's no View
Controller transitions.

00:25:00.036 --> 00:25:02.126
So what you need to
do there is instead

00:25:02.126 --> 00:25:04.366
of setting an automatic
Interstitial Presentation

00:25:04.366 --> 00:25:07.316
Policy, you set a Manual
Presentation Policy.

00:25:07.936 --> 00:25:10.476
And what this does, is it
still enables interstitials

00:25:10.476 --> 00:25:13.286
to present automatically
and seamlessly, but you need

00:25:13.286 --> 00:25:15.106
to request the presentation.

00:25:15.676 --> 00:25:18.556
So if you're building a
game style application,

00:25:19.006 --> 00:25:22.186
when you transition
from, say, the game back

00:25:22.186 --> 00:25:24.476
into the menu would
be one example.

00:25:24.696 --> 00:25:27.036
You can call Request
Interstitial Presentation,

00:25:27.036 --> 00:25:31.936
and if an ad is available,
it will present.

00:25:31.936 --> 00:25:34.396
One thing to bear in mind
with interstitial ads is

00:25:34.396 --> 00:25:38.176
that when you're setting this
property on View Controllers

00:25:38.176 --> 00:25:40.146
that might happen quite a while

00:25:40.146 --> 00:25:42.006
after the user has
launched the application.

00:25:42.546 --> 00:25:45.226
Setting the property on a View
Controller is really the only

00:25:45.226 --> 00:25:47.356
way for the iAd framework
to know

00:25:47.356 --> 00:25:49.706
that ad requests
should stop being sent

00:25:49.776 --> 00:25:51.116
to the iAd App Network.

00:25:51.616 --> 00:25:54.336
So what you can do
to improve on this is

00:25:54.336 --> 00:25:57.976
to call Prepare Interstitial
Ads early

00:25:57.976 --> 00:25:59.786
on in your application's
lifecycle

00:25:59.786 --> 00:26:02.216
so that you don't miss
those early impressions.

00:26:02.876 --> 00:26:05.546
And with that, I'm going

00:26:05.546 --> 00:26:07.516
to bring David back
up to do a demo.

